post.title: What is "ig" and "kek", and how do you use them in sentences?

body: I thought ig was Instagram... apparently it's "I guess". It doesn't flow off the tongue like most internet lingo. Kek started as the "in the know" way to say "lol" on 4chan. Lol had fallen off pretty hard on 4chan due to "normies" using the term. "kek" was originally used in world of warcraft to replace "lol" if the reader was alliance and the speaker was horde.

post.title: What is "ig" and "kek", and how do you use them in sentences?

body:
Kek used to mean lol. Nowadays its usage has evolved a bit beyond a simple 'lol'. It is usually used to signal that a situation is funny, but in an edgy/meme-y/dank kind of way, which is why it has seen a lot of use on 4chan.

An example:
Bob - "Red has been doing the floss again"
Alice - "kek" (because the floss is a meme/edgy, it is funny, but more ackin to a snicker than an overt laugh)

post.title: What is "ig" and "kek", and how do you use them in sentences?

body: A long time ago Koreans would play their national sport, Starcraft, against English speaking people. Instead of saying things like hehehehe they would say kekekeke because their keyboards didn't have an H button. Blizzard decided to make kek the Orcish word for lol. Later 4chan learned of an ancient Egyptian primordial frog-headed god of chaos named Kek and used meme magic to summon him. Kek, having arisen again in full glory after millennia of neglect, proceeded to shoot a gorilla, install Donald Trump in the White House, and create hurricane Irma.
